\int_{-4}^{-2}e^{-x}\,dx
\begin{align} \int e^{-x}\,dx=&\int\frac{1}{e^x}\,dx\\=&\ln|e^x|\\\\\int_{-4}^{-2}e^{-x}\,dx=&\left(\ln|e^{-2}|\right)-\left(\ln|e^{-4}|\right)\\=&-2+4\\=&2 \end{align}
 \int_{-4}^{-2} e^{-x} dx = \left . \left ( -e^{-x}\right ) \right |_{-4}^{-2} = -e^2+e^4 = e^2 \left ( e^2-1\right ) 
u=-x
dx=-du
